article.headline: Bradley 88, Wright State 49
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- J.J. Tauai scored 15 points to lead six Bradley players in double-figure scoring as the Braves rolled over Wright State 88-49 Tuesday night. Jeremy Crouch scored 14 points for Bradley (6-3), 12 of them off 4-for-7 three-point shooting. Will Franklin and Daniel Ruffin added 13 points each, while Matt Salley and Andrew Warren chipped in 12 apiece. DaShaun Wood's 10 points made him the only player in double figures for the Raiders (2-3), who shot just 9-for-31 (29 percent) in the first half and finished 21-for-64 (33 percent) for the game. The Braves, who led 40-21 at halftime, capitalized on Wright State mistakes -- scoring 22 points off turnovers compared with just four points off turnovers for the Raiders. Wright State didn't manage a basket in the last 4:37 of the game.
